Cell.Text: G|This isn't the time. There's already a fight scheduled right now, and as usual these cowards aren't worth the dirt they fight on. | Tell you what. Go. Watch this next fight. See if you think you can do any better, then come back if you haven't soiled yourself.

You think you're worthy of my Pit? | Look around you. These are some of the finest warriors in Skyrim. | They could make fortunes as mercenaries, but they fight here for greater honor in Sovngarde. | You really think you can match ranks with them?

Node.Caption: ArenaHukiJoinArenaBranchTopic: I want to fight in the Pit.

Cell.Text: First time in Windhelm? This is the Pit. | Here, we battle. Some for glory, some for freedom, some for coin.
I try to mold these pathetic icebrains into something of worth. | The Pit is not a place for cowards, or children. I make sure the fights are something that deserves an audience.
The money goes with the glory. Triumph fills both the pocket and the spirit.

All over the hold, rats make their way here, to my Pit. | Steal a sweetroll. Kill a man. Doesn't matter once you're here. | If you can prove yourself worthy, and give the crowd something to forget the cold for a time, you earn the right to walk out.
Bold words from an Imperial dog.
Bold words from a mongrel Breton dog.
Bold words from a Redguard dog.
Bold words from an elven dog.
Bold words from an Ashlander.
Bold words for an Argonian this far from the Black Marsh.
This isn't your home, Khajiit. There won't be any moon sugar to comfort you when you lie bleeding.
Bold words, brother.
Bold words, sister.

Node.Caption: ArenaQuestJoinOhYeahJustWatchMe: They could aspire to match ranks with me.

Cell.Text: [S] G|But it's not my choice how you choose to die. | Get in there. If the animals don't rip you apart, you'll have earned the right to keep trying until they do.

[S] G|That's right. And until you do, you're Pit Meat. | As worthless as an animal. Until you prove otherwise, you'll fight the other animals. | Pray they don't rip you apart like the last brave idiot who wandered in here.

Node.Caption: ArenaQuestHukiJustLetMeTry: I only hope to reach their heights.

Cell.Text: G|What do you expect from an Imperial dog? Without the legion at your back, you're as weak as a child.
G|Of course, the Breton backs down in the face of glory. No surprises there.
G|I expected better of you, Redguard. Walk out of my bloodworks while you still can.
G|I should have expected an elf to run away at the first sign of a fight. Probably best that you don't come back here.
G|After your home burned, Ashlander, I thought you'd be eager to prove your worth in a new land. I guess it's true what they say about your kind.
G|That's right, slither back to the Black Marsh with the rest of your kind.
G|Aww, I was looking forward to making a rug from your hide.
G|There's not room for everyone in Sovngarde, brother.
G|There's not room for everyone in Sovngarde, sister.
